{"lemma":"كَعْكَةُ","slug":"كَعْكَةُ","root":"ك.ع.ك","root_slug":"ك-ع-ك","root_link":"/words/roots/ك-ع-ك","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n43053"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%83%D9%8E%D8%B9%D9%92%D9%83%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"cake(s)","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"biscuits, tarts, buns, twists","tags":["collective"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from or cognate with Aramaic כַּעְכָּא / ܟܥܟܐ (kaʿkā, “cake, loaf”), from Akkadian 𒈖 (kukku, “cake, loaf, pastry, lump of dough”), ultimately from Sumerian 𒈖 (gug, “offering; cake”). A widespread wanderwort found in many language families, Egyptian ꜥkk, ꜥq (“a type of loaf”) and Proto-Indo-European *gag- / *gōg- (“round, ball-shaped object; lump; clump”), likely distant cognate with English cake."},"ipa":["/kaʕk/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n43053","headword_ar":"كَعْكٌ","root":"kEk","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A well-known bread;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"biscuit;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA;) or ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a kind of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dry bread:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA, TA:) now applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sort of bread made in the form of a ring, hollow,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and generally containing some"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dbs","text_ar":"دبس"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the best of which is brought from Syria, and given as a present."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["MA","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}